description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an innovative motivated endoscopy technician to join our friendly endoscopy team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a JAG accredited unit providing Bowel Cancer screening for South East London. We have 4 procedure rooms and will be expanding the unit due to increase work load.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a busy unit providing therapeutic, diagnostic and emergency service for both Inpatients as well as outpatients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have an excellent interpersonal relationship and communication skills and the ability to use their initiative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous endoscopy experience in decontamination is desirable but not essential as we provide all in-house training using an endoscopy competency program and an experience mentor is assigned to support you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant must be comfortable working in a team environment as well as being able to work autonomously and demonstrate high levels of patient care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information please contact Adeola Bilewu Nursing Sister on contact number 0208333 3000 ext. 6840/8636&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Adeola Bilewu&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:Endoscopy Manager&lt;/p&gt;
